## Check-in and Check-out

Empress details:

-   Check-in is 2pm

-   Check-out is Noon -¬†

-   Late check out After 2:00pm is available upon request until 6:00pm = 500 Baht fee

-   Check Out after 6:00pm = the Rate of one extra night

If you arrive before your check in time, you can store your bags with The Empress Staff. This is the same for if you need to store your bags after you have checked out.

## How much do rooms cost?

Empress (per person, includes breakfast and lunch 27 October - 1 November)

Price is per person.¬†

-   Deluxe single - $440 USD

-   Deluxe shared - $250 USD (per person)

-   Superior shared - $205 USD (per person)

-   Superior single - $350 USD

--------------------------
## How much are extra nights?

Superior: $60 per room per night ($30 each for a shared room)

Deluxe: $80 per room per night ($40 each for a shared room)

Includes breakfast.


-----------------
## What is included?


Breakfast is included with your stay.

Lunch is included during the conference.¬†

Dinner is not included, but there are many affordable dining options nearby.

# üì¢For Exhibitors

Exhibitions at the BT Conference are reserved for parties having a professional link to Bible Translation.

Note: Canvassing or distributing advertising materials or souvenirs in the exhibit hall by representatives of non-exhibiting parties is not allowed.

## What's included in the app?
---------------------------

### Exhibitor Listing

-   Dedicated profile page.

-   Company name, logo, description, and contact info.

-   Can include links to website, social media, and promotional materials.

-   Exhibitors can message attendees

-   Attendees can schedule meetings

### Interactive Floor Plan

-   Exhibitor booth location is pinned on the event map.

-   Attendees can tap a booth on the map to view the exhibitor's profile.

# üìù Registration
## When can I register?
Click **Sign Up** on the home page and follow the instructions to create an account using your email.

## Refund Policy
Requests for cancellation and refund of registration must be received by May 31, 2025. Such registrants will receive a full refund, less a $10 administration fee. After May 31, onsite registration will be transferred to online registration, with the difference refunded. (Note: Online registration allows full access to pre-recorded presentations, ppts, papers and handouts during and after the conference).

## App

We are using Guidebook. The app is posted at <https://builder.guidebook.com/g/#/guides/btc25/details>

Once you are registered, you should receive an invitation to the Guide along with a login link.

--------------------
## Online Participation

Online attendees will have Zoom access to all the live presenters. We'll also show the videos of online presenters.

Plenaries and their sign language interpreters will be recorded and those recordings will be made available.

We'll upload the links to videos in Guidebook on the day of their presentation and they will be accessible in the app long after the conference.

More on how to use Guidebook: <https://support.guidebook.com/hc/en-us/articles/360056582614-Guidebook-Web-for-End-Users>

Note: If a speaker doesn't provide their pre-recorded presentation, you won't find a video in their session details.

The Friday banquet with Freddy Boswell is NOT be broadcast on Zoom.

* * * * *
## Joining Zoom Rooms

Sessions with Zoom options should show a way to access the Zoom room.

## Absent Presenters

If a presenter is unable to be there and . . . 

-   the moderator is familiar with the topic, they may field the questions themselves

-   there are colleagues of the presenter there, they may answer on the presenter's behalf

-   neither of those are the case, the session may dismiss earlier and attendees either have informal discussions amongst themselves or move on to the next thing/enjoy a short break

* * * * *

## When can I see recorded presentations?

If a speaker has submitted a pre-recorded presentation, it will be available in the app.

Recorded sessions will be uploaded to the proceedings by the end of 2025. Most sessions will be recorded.
